reviews.text: Best place for leaving,parks,swimming pool,hiking route...it’s a place where is not that much pollution:)👍👍👍

It's kind of old, and not really close to anything. It's also up on a hill...and kind of smells too. It definitely feels claustrophobic in the corridors. This housing estate is kind of old. Did I mention that it's old yet? There is also a relatively massive nursing home on one of the lower floors of part of the estate. Now, the units themselves feel quite spacious by Hong Kong standards, so there's that. So if you are willing to remodel the interior of you unit, you will actually have a decent piece of paradise amongst all the pollution, humidity, and overpopulation of Hong Kong.

I stay there for 2weeks every year. It is located in the middle of the hill. Traffic is convenient. Supe market is there as well as some char chan ting. Very quiet with excellent air quality. The residents are very friendly. Very safe place to stay.
Most people leave us a middle class have stable income none of them are on garment worker

reviews.text: 這裡有一個康文署公衆泳池專供荃威花園住客使用，非常有特色。
非常理想的居住環境，住客可以養寵物， 區內樓宇平台相連非常寬敞， 三層停車場車位充足， 位於大帽山腳 荃灣市中心之上 所以空氣特別清新。
位處山腰，空氣清新。
環境清靜，交通太少路線
單位大間隔實用
